{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "vLLM is a high-throughput inference engine for large language models. Its core innovation, PagedAttention, eliminates memory fragmentation in the KV cache and achieves 3–4× more throughput than naive implementations at the same GPU memory budget. It supports OpenAI-compatible serving, offline batch inference, async FastAPI integration, and multi-GPU tensor parallelism."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "vLLM architecture: request queue → scheduler (continuous batching, KV-block allocator) → GPU execution (PagedAttention, tensor parallel, prefix caching) → output streams; deployment modes and PagedAttention detail"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why KV Cache Management Matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "During autoregressive generation, each transformer layer caches the Key and Value tensors for every previously generated token. This KV cache grows token-by-token and is the primary GPU memory consumer during inference — not the model weights, which are static."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Traditional implementations pre-allocate one contiguous buffer per request sized at "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "max_seq_len × num_layers × 2 × hidden_dim"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". When requests finish early, that memory is wasted until the slot is freed. When batch sizes vary, internal fragmentation means 60–80% of GPU memory can be unusable at any given moment."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PagedAttention"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PagedAttention divides the KV cache into fixed-size blocks (pages), like virtual memory in an OS. Each sequence is assigned a logical block table that maps logical block IDs to physical GPU memory pages. Pages are allocated incrementally as tokens are generated and freed immediately when a sequence finishes — with no fragmentation."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Because the mapping is virtual, sequences can share physical pages (useful for prefix caching and beam search), and a single GPU's memory can fit many more concurrent sequences, increasing throughput without degrading output quality."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Installation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Requires Python 3.9+, CUDA 11.8+ or ROCm 5.6+\npip install vllm\n\n# Check GPU is visible\npython -c \"import torch; print(torch.cuda.get_device_name(0))\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Offline Batch Inference"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "LLM"}, {"type": "text", "text": " class is the simplest entry point. Pass a list of prompts and get back a list of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "RequestOutput"}, {"type": "text", "text": " objects. Use this for batch jobs where latency per request is less important than total throughput."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from vllm import LLM, SamplingParams\n\nllm = LLM(\n    model=\"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n    tensor_parallel_size=1,          # number of GPUs\n    max_model_len=8192,              # max sequence length to allocate KV for\n    gpu_memory_utilization=0.90,     # fraction of GPU RAM to use for KV cache\n)\n\nprompts = [\n    \"Summarize the following article: ...\",\n    \"Translate to French: Hello, world!\",\n    \"Write a unit test for this function: ...\",\n]\n\nparams = SamplingParams(\n    temperature=0.7,\n    top_p=0.9,\n    max_tokens=512,\n    stop=[\"</s>\", \"<|eot_id|>\"],\n)\n\noutputs = llm.generate(prompts, params)\n\nfor output in outputs:\n    prompt = output.prompt\n    generated = output.outputs[0].text\n    print(f\"Prompt: {prompt[:40]}...\")\n    print(f\"Output: {generated[:80]}...\\n\")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "SamplingParams"}, {"type": "text", "text": " fields:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "temperature"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "float"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0 = greedy, higher = more random"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "top_p"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "float"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Nucleus sampling cutoff"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "max_tokens"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "int"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Maximum tokens to generate per request"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "stop"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "list[str]"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stop sequences (model-specific EOS tokens)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "n"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "int"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Number of completions per prompt (output.outputs has N items)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "presence_penalty"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "float"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Penalise tokens already present in the output"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "OpenAI-Compatible HTTP Server"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start a server that exposes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/v1/completions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/v1/chat/completions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/v1/embeddings"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — fully compatible with any OpenAI SDK client."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Launch the server\nvllm serve meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct \\\n    --host 0.0.0.0 \\\n    --port 8000 \\\n    --tensor-parallel-size 1 \\\n    --max-model-len 8192 \\\n    --gpu-memory-utilization 0.90\n\n# Test with curl\ncurl http://localhost:8000/v1/chat/completions \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d '{\n      \"model\": \"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n      \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello!\"}],\n      \"stream\": false\n    }'"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use the OpenAI Python SDK by pointing it at the vLLM server:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from openai import OpenAI\n\nclient = OpenAI(\n    base_url=\"http://localhost:8000/v1\",\n    api_key=\"not-required\",           # vLLM does not check this by default\n)\n\n# Non-streaming chat\nresponse = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Explain PagedAttention in one sentence.\"}],\n    max_tokens=200,\n    temperature=0.0,\n)\nprint(response.choices[0].message.content)\n\n# Streaming chat\nstream = client.chat.completions.create(\n    model=\"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Count from 1 to 5.\"}],\n    stream=True,\n)\nfor chunk in stream:\n    delta = chunk.choices[0].delta.content\n    if delta:\n        print(delta, end=\"\", flush=True)\nprint()"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AsyncLLMEngine for FastAPI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When embedding vLLM inside your own FastAPI application, use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "AsyncLLMEngine"}, {"type": "text", "text": " directly. It runs the scheduler in a background event loop and yields tokens as they are generated."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import asyncio\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom fastapi.responses import StreamingResponse\nfrom vllm.engine.arg_utils import AsyncEngineArgs\nfrom vllm.engine.async_llm_engine import AsyncLLMEngine\nfrom vllm import SamplingParams\nimport uuid\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\nengine_args = AsyncEngineArgs(\n    model=\"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n    tensor_parallel_size=1,\n    max_model_len=4096,\n    gpu_memory_utilization=0.90,\n)\nengine = AsyncLLMEngine.from_engine_args(engine_args)\n\n\n@app.post(\"/generate\")\nasync def generate(prompt: str, max_tokens: int = 256):\n    request_id = str(uuid.uuid4())\n    params = SamplingParams(temperature=0.7, max_tokens=max_tokens)\n\n    async def token_stream():\n        async for output in engine.generate(prompt, params, request_id):\n            if output.outputs:\n                token_text = output.outputs[0].text\n                yield token_text\n            if output.finished:\n                break\n\n    return StreamingResponse(token_stream(), media_type=\"text/plain\")\n\n\n@app.post(\"/chat\")\nasync def chat(system: str, user: str, max_tokens: int = 512):\n    # Apply chat template manually (or use tokenizer.apply_chat_template)\n    prompt = f\"<|system|>{system}</s><|user|>{user}</s><|assistant|>\"\n    request_id = str(uuid.uuid4())\n    params = SamplingParams(temperature=0.0, max_tokens=max_tokens, stop=[\"</s>\"])\n\n    full_response = \"\"\n    async for output in engine.generate(prompt, params, request_id):\n        if output.outputs:\n            full_response = output.outputs[0].text\n    return {\"response\": full_response}"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multi-GPU Tensor Parallelism"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For models too large for a single GPU, vLLM supports tensor parallelism — splitting each weight matrix column-wise across N GPUs. Each GPU holds "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "1/N"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of every attention and FFN layer. An all-reduce operation synchronises activations at each layer boundary. This is transparent to callers — the API surface is identical."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Offline: split a 70B model across 4 × A100 80GB\nllm = LLM(\n    model=\"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct\",\n    tensor_parallel_size=4,\n    max_model_len=32768,\n    gpu_memory_utilization=0.92,\n)\n\n# Server: same flag\n# vllm serve meta-llama/Llama-3.1-70B-Instruct --tensor-parallel-size 4"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "vLLM also supports pipeline parallelism ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pipeline_parallel_size"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") for stacking layers across GPUs connected by NVLink, and the two can be combined. For most deployments, tensor parallelism alone is sufficient."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prefix Caching"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When many requests share an identical prefix (e.g. a long system prompt or a few-shot examples block), vLLM can cache the KV blocks for that prefix and reuse them across requests. Only the per-request suffix triggers new computation."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "llm = LLM(\n    model=\"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n    enable_prefix_caching=True,     # hash-based block deduplication\n    max_model_len=8192,\n)\n\nSYSTEM_PROMPT = \"You are an expert Python engineer. \" + (\"Context: \" * 100)  # 800-token prefix\n\n# Requests sharing this prefix pay compute cost once; subsequent requests hit the cache\nqueries = [\n    f\"{SYSTEM_PROMPT} Q: {q}\"\n    for q in [\"Explain list comprehensions.\", \"What is a generator?\"]\n]\n\noutputs = llm.generate(queries, SamplingParams(temperature=0.0, max_tokens=200))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Quantization"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "vLLM supports several quantization formats to reduce GPU memory usage at the cost of a small accuracy degradation."}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Format"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Bits"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to enable"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Notes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AWQ"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4-bit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "quantization=\"awq\""}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Activation-aware, best quality/speed tradeoff"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPTQ"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4-bit / 3-bit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "quantization=\"gptq\""}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Widely available pre-quantized models on HF Hub"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "FP8"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "8-bit float"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "quantization=\"fp8\""}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "H100/H200 only, near-BF16 quality, 2× throughput"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "bitsandbytes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4-bit / 8-bit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "quantization=\"bitsandbytes\""}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NF4/INT8 loading; slower than AWQ but no pre-quantization step needed"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Load an AWQ-quantized model (pre-quantized versions available on HuggingFace)\nllm = LLM(\n    model=\"casperhansen/llama-3-8b-instruct-awq\",\n    quantization=\"awq\",\n    max_model_len=8192,\n)\n\n# Or quantize on the fly with bitsandbytes (no separate quant step required)\nllm = LLM(\n    model=\"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n    quantization=\"bitsandbytes\",\n    load_format=\"bitsandbytes\",\n    max_model_len=8192,\n)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LangChain Integration"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The simplest approach is to point LangChain's OpenAI-compatible chat class at the vLLM server. This works with chains, agents, and structured output."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\nfrom langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, SystemMessage\nfrom langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\nfrom langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\n\n# Point LangChain at the local vLLM server\nllm = ChatOpenAI(\n    model=\"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n    base_url=\"http://localhost:8000/v1\",\n    api_key=\"not-required\",\n    temperature=0.0,\n    streaming=True,\n)\n\n# Simple chain\nprompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n    (\"system\", \"You are a concise technical writer.\"),\n    (\"human\", \"Explain {concept} in two sentences.\"),\n])\nchain = prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\n\nresult = chain.invoke({\"concept\": \"PagedAttention\"})\nprint(result)\n\n# Structured output (requires a capable model)\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\n\nclass TechSummary(BaseModel):\n    title: str\n    key_benefit: str\n    use_case: str\n\nstructured_llm = llm.with_structured_output(TechSummary)\nsummary = structured_llm.invoke(\"Describe vLLM as a tech summary.\")\nprint(summary.key_benefit)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Monitoring Throughput and Latency"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The vLLM server exposes a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "/metrics"}, {"type": "text", "text": " endpoint in Prometheus format. Key metrics to track:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vllm:request_success_total"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — total completed requests. Useful for computing request throughput rate."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vllm:e2e_request_latency_seconds"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — end-to-end latency histogram (time to first token + generation)."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vllm:generation_tokens_total"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — total output tokens generated; divide by time for tok/s throughput."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vllm:gpu_cache_usage_perc"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — fraction of KV cache blocks in use. Near 100% means the scheduler is frequently preempting — consider reducing max concurrency."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vllm:num_requests_running / waiting"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — batch size in flight and queue depth."}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "curl -s http://localhost:8000/metrics | grep vllm:gpu_cache_usage\n# vllm:gpu_cache_usage_perc{model_name=\"...\",} 0.42"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "vLLM vs Ollama: When to Use Each"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dimension"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "vLLM"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Ollama"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Target environment"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Linux server with CUDA GPU"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mac (Metal), Windows, Linux desktop"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Throughput"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Highest: PagedAttention + continuous batching"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Good for 1 user; degrades under load"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multi-GPU"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Native tensor parallelism across N GPUs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limited; best on single GPU"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model formats"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "HuggingFace (safetensors/PyTorch), AWQ, GPTQ, FP8"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GGUF only"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Setup friction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pip install + CUDA driver; models from HF Hub"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One-line installer; ollama pull <model>"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Serving concurrent users"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Designed for it (continuous batching)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential by default"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best use case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Production API serving, batch jobs, large models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Local development, personal tooling, offline chat"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Production Deployment Pattern"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A typical production setup runs vLLM behind a reverse proxy with health checking, auto-restart, and a shared API key check layer."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# docker-compose.yml snippet\n# services:\n#   vllm:\n#     image: vllm/vllm-openai:latest\n#     command: [\n#       \"--model\", \"meta-llama/Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct\",\n#       \"--tensor-parallel-size\", \"1\",\n#       \"--max-model-len\", \"8192\",\n#       \"--api-key\", \"my-secret-key\",      # enable auth\n#       \"--served-model-name\", \"llama3\",   # alias for clients\n#     ]\n#     runtime: nvidia\n#     ports: [\"8000:8000\"]\n#     volumes: [\"/data/hf-cache:/root/.cache/huggingface\"]\n#     healthcheck:\n#       test: [\"CMD\", \"curl\", \"-f\", \"http://localhost:8000/health\"]\n\n# Ping the health endpoint\nimport httpx\n\nasync def check_vllm_health(base_url: str = \"http://localhost:8000\") -> bool:\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        try:\n            r = await client.get(f\"{base_url}/health\", timeout=5.0)\n            return r.status_code == 200\n        except httpx.ConnectError:\n            return False"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Environment Variable Reference"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variable"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "HF_TOKEN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "HuggingFace auth token for gated models (Llama, Gemma)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Restrict which GPU indices vLLM can see (e.g. \"0,1\")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "VLLM_WORKER_MULTIPROC_METHOD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Set to \"spawn\" if tensor-parallel workers hang on startup"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "VLLM_ATTENTION_BACKEND"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Override attention kernel (FLASH_ATTN, FLASHINFER, XFORMERS)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Pitfalls"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "OOM at startup"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": vLLM pre-allocates KV blocks to fill "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "gpu_memory_utilization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of VRAM. Start at 0.85 and lower if the process crashes. Also reduce "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "max_model_len"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — it linearly controls block pool size."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model not found on HF Hub"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Llama 3 and Gemma require accepting the license on huggingface.co and setting "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "HF_TOKEN"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Wrong chat template"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": When using raw "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "LLM.generate()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", you must manually apply the model's chat template. Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "tokenizer.apply_chat_template(messages, tokenize=False)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from the HuggingFace tokenizer, or use the OpenAI-compatible server which handles this."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Slow first request"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": CUDA kernels are JIT-compiled on first inference. Send a warmup request during server startup if latency consistency matters."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Tensor parallel size mismatch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "tensor_parallel_size"}, {"type": "text", "text": " must evenly divide the model's attention heads. Most 8B/13B/70B models work with 1, 2, 4, or 8. Check "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "config.json"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "num_attention_heads"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to verify divisibility."}]}]}]}]}}